result.execSummary:
The defendant Willmarvin Diaz-Boria was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: The Court ordered restitution in the stipulated amount of $75.00 payable to Aaron R.--to be paid first/bail to apply. Restitution is joint and several with all co-actors convicted of this offense (Abigail Baez--14CF292/Mary Molale--14CF294/Jeriel Rodriguez--14CF295/Erik Tejada--14CF296).

Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs--bail to apply after restitution paid. Pay all supervision fees. The Court ordered that all financail obligations and restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

The defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program AFTER SERVING THE FIRST 18 MONTHS OF THIS SENTENCE
Consecutive to: to any other time being served with credit for 5 days served.

superMiscConds.notes: Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment.
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions: Firearm possession and Voting

No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses).
No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
No contact with victims Aaron R., Alexandre J.-S., Elizabeth L., Karissa H., Mitchell H. and co-actors Mary Molale, Erik Tejada, Jeriel Rodriguez, and Abigail Baez.

Cooperate with random urine screens.
Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent.
Participate in Cognitive Thinking.
Provide DNA sample--pay surcharge.
Obtain AODA assessment and if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment.

Sentencing Hearing set for 8-04-14 at 8:30 a.m. RESCHEDULED to 8-04-14 at 1:30 p.m. before Branch 21.  No objection from the parties.

Attorney Mark S Rosen appears telephonically.  Benjamin A. Wesson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Matter before the Court on defense motion (oral) to adjourn sentencing hearing.  Telephone conference held off the record in chambers.  On the record.  Defense motion heard; state takes no position.  The Court denies motion to adjourn at this time for reasons set forth on the record.  Case remains set for Sentencing Hearing on 8-04-14 at 8:30 a.m. before Branch 21.

Defendant Willmarvin Diaz-Boria in court with Attorney Mark S Rosen.  Benjamin A Wesson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

On motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 1 AMENDED to: ROBBERY, PTAC- AS PARTY TO A CRIME, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.32 (1)(a), a Class E Felony.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting. 

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the state, the Court ordered Counts 2 and 3 DISMISSED and Counts 2, 3, and uncharged offense READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing.

Presentence Investigation Report ordered.  The Court reiterated to the defendant that the no-contact order is to be complied with as a condition of bail.  Filed, Order for PSI.
  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 4, 2014 at 08:30 am.
